-- Nomura Hires Schroder’s Catalano as Metal, Mining Research Head
-- B y   F i r a t   K a y a k i r a n
-- 2012-09-24T09:05:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-24/nomura-hires-schroder-s-catalano-as-metal-mining-research-head.html
Nomura Holdings Inc. hired Sam Catalano as the head of metals and mining research for Europe,
the  Middle East  and Africa.  Catalano, who worked at  Schroders Plc (SDR)  as a global resources
analyst, will start as a managing director on Oct. 15 and report
to Graeme Pearson, Nomura’s head of equity research, the
Japanese bank said today in an e-mailed statement. Catalano has
worked for Macquarie Group Ltd. and Morgan Stanley, Nomura said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Firat Kayakiran in London at 
